org.itemscript.core.values
Interface PutResponse

All Known Implementing Classes:
ItemscriptPutResponse
public interface PutResponse

A representation of the response to a JsonPutAccess.putValue(java.lang.String, org.itemscript.core.values.JsonValue) operation.

Author:
Jacob Davies
jacob@itemscript.org

Method Summary
 JsonObject meta()
          Any additional metadata that was returned from the put operation.
 java.lang.String url()
          The actual URL that the value was put under, which may differ from the URL that was supplied to JsonPutAccess.putValue(java.lang.String, org.itemscript.core.values.JsonValue) in the event that the URL contained a query string.
 JsonValue value()
          If applicable, the actual JsonValue that was put, or null if the value is not available.
 

Method Detail

meta

JsonObject meta()
Any additional metadata that was returned from the put operation.

Returns:
A JsonObject containing metadata, or null if no metadata was available.

url

java.lang.String url()
The actual URL that the value was put under, which may differ from the URL that was supplied to JsonPutAccess.putValue(java.lang.String, org.itemscript.core.values.JsonValue) in the event that the URL contained a query string.

Returns:
The actual URL that the value was put under.

value

JsonValue value()
If applicable, the actual JsonValue that was put, or null if the value is not available. If available, the response may be treated as a valid copy of the actual value after being put. If null, the actual value must be retrieved with JsonGetAccess.getValue(java.lang.String).

Returns:
The actual JsonValue representing the resource after being put, or null if not available.
